    "summary": "In the past 20 years I developed myself as a Finance all-rounder. My experience includes Financial Accounting, Management Accounting, Auditing and Controlling. I have broad experience in working in and managing of small professional teams, large operational teams and project teams. I am specialized in IFRS and experienced in US GAAP as well as sundry local GAAP\u2019s. On numerous occasions I managed the introduction and/or transformation from local GAAP to IFRS and US GAAP.\n\nDuring my assignments I redesigned work processes of Finance functions (realizing significant cost saving of up to 40%), integrated Finance departments within a foreign branch of a financial service provider (Banking, Insurance,  Pensions and Leasing) and implemented a European market risk management system. I set up a Financial Accounting Shared Service Center, which managed the Financial Accounting and International Reporting processes of three countries (Russia, Hungary and Bulgaria) and created an Accounting and Reporting Centre of Excellence within a large international EB consultancy firm. Finally I participated in project teams that were responsible for introduction to the NYSE and responsible for the sale of the retail activities of a large financial service provider.\n\nMy earlier auditing background with the Big Four firms give me a wide exposure and experience in different industry types in most sectors. My experience within the financial services industry give me in depth knowledge of amongst other life insurance, leasing and corporate banking. In my present function I gained specialized knowledge of IFRS and the enforcement of IFRS both locally as on European level. \n\nMy general business skills I developed at Insead where I finished the Young Management program.\n\nMy academic skills are best illustrated by the sundry articles I published, the conferences on which I acted as a speaker and my ongoing PhD research in the field of Pension Accounting.\n\nSpecialties: Financial accounting and reporting, team building, education and presentation skills, change management, consulting. Board room level exposure.",
